<BaseLayout title="Bearded Dragon Setup Guide" description="Everything you need to create a comfortable habitat for bearded dragons.">
  <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Bearded Dragon Setup Guide</h2>
  <p class="mb-4">Bearded dragons require spacious enclosures with proper heating, lighting, and substrates. Follow this guide to build a happy home.</p>
  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Enclosure</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">Adult bearded dragons need a 75–120 gallon tank. Provide a secure screen lid and a basking area.</p>
  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Lighting & Heating</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">Use a basking bulb to create a hot spot of 95–105°F and a UVB bulb for 10–12 hours daily.</p>
  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Substrate</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">Choose reptile carpet, tile, or paper towels. Avoid loose substrates like sand to prevent impaction.</p>
  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Decor & Accessories</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">Add branches, rocks, and hide boxes to encourage natural behaviors. Include a shallow water dish.</p>
  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Recommended Products</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mb-4">
    <li>75 Gallon Reptile Terrarium</li>
    <li>High-Quality UVB Fixture</li>
    <li>Basking Dome with Ceramic Heat Emitter</li>
    <li>Reptile Carpet</li>
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>